business_analysis.business_domain: Local peer-to-peer marketplace platform enabling individuals to buy and sell used and new items within their communities
business_analysis.business_model: Commission-based marketplace with revenue from promoted listings, shipping services, transaction fees, and premium seller features. Facilitates local commerce between individual buyers and sellers across multiple product categories.
key_products_services: Local marketplace mobile app and web platform
Seller verification and trust & safety features
business_analysis.target_customers: Individual consumers looking to buy or sell used and new items locally, including casual sellers decluttering homes, small resellers, vehicle dealers, and bargain hunters seeking deals on secondhand goods

key_entities.description: Individual buyers and sellers on the platform, with profiles, ratings, and transaction history

key_entities.name: categories

key_entities.name: messages
key_entities.description: In-app communications between buyers and sellers for negotiation and coordination

key_entities.name: locations
key_entities.description: Geographic data for local marketplace matching (city, state, zip code level)

key_entities.name: reviews_ratings
key_entities.description: User feedback and reputation scores for trust and safety

key_entities.name: promotions
key_entities.description: Paid advertising placements for featured listings

key_entities.name: shipments
key_entities.description: Delivery tracking for items shipped through OfferUp's shipping service

data_products.name: Seller Analytics Dashboard
data_products.description: Performance metrics for sellers including views, favorites, messages, and sales conversion

data_products.name: Marketplace Insights
data_products.description: Category trends, pricing insights, and demand signals for buyers and sellers

data_products.name: Trust & Safety Monitoring
data_products.description: Fraud detection, user verification, and platform safety metrics

primary_use_cases: Marketplace health monitoring and GMV tracking
Geographic demand mapping and local market insights
Inventory turnover and listing lifecycle analysis
business_questions: What is our GMV by category, geography, and time period?
Which categories have the highest conversion rates and fastest time to sale?
What are the pricing trends for popular items like vehicles and electronics?
How do promoted listings perform vs organic listings in terms of views and sales?
What is the buyer-to-seller ratio in different geographic markets?
Which user cohorts have the highest lifetime value and repeat transaction rates?
What percentage of listings result in completed transactions?
How does search behavior correlate with successful transactions?
What are the peak listing and buying times by day/week/season?
Which markets have supply-demand imbalances we can address?
What is the fraud rate and how effective are our trust & safety measures?
How do shipping vs local pickup transactions differ in completion rates?
What drives user churn and how can we improve retention?
Which acquisition channels bring the highest quality buyers and sellers?

Demonstrate category performance analysis with pricing trends and demand signals
Create geographic heat maps showing local market activity and opportunities
Show seller segmentation and performance scoring for targeted engagement
Analyze conversion funnels from search to message to transaction
Build cohort analysis showing user retention and repeat transaction patterns
Demonstrate fraud detection patterns using behavioral and transactional anomalies
Create dynamic pricing recommendations based on historical sales data
Show seasonal trend analysis for inventory planning and marketing
Build a real-time listing performance tracker for sellers
Demonstrate A/B test analysis for promoted listing effectiveness
Create supply-demand matching algorithms for marketplace optimization
